I’ll tell ya a little secret about exercise

It helped me pass through a very rough patch of depression in my life due to how it “fixes” mental health.

There’s a saying by a lot of doctors that if you could turn the effects of exercise into a pill, it would be the MOST prescribed substance in the world. It’s magic

So there’s the dumb dumb way of approaching this and there’s the intelligent way of doing it. Most people would say “take up running or gym!”

Yes, those are good, but they often are boring as batshit and take so much willpower

So here’s the tip: find a sport or physical activity that you love and think is the best thing ever. Something that gives you another enjoyable reason to get up. That way you look forward to it, AND you get the mental health benefits

For me it was boxing. I used to do regular gym and it started to get very boring and grindy, but boxing is amazing fun, it’s tremendously hard and painful but I love the challenge and I love improving, and seeing a boxer move fluidly is like watching ballet, there’s a beauty to it you really appreciate

Anyway there will be something out there you’re sure to love, and you’ll be glad you found it, it makes existing a little bit easier
